* Introduction
** Desired Operation
On startup, Emacs loads the file =init.el= located in the =~/.emacs.d/= directory.  =init.el= specifies the path to the most recent version of [[http://org-mode.org][Org-Mode]], and instructs Emacs to load and run all the *.org files in the =~/.emacs.d/= directory.  Emacs will execute the Emacs Lisp statements delimited by the =begin_src= and =end_src= blocks within an .org file.

** Dependencies
1) The file =init.el= must be placed in the =~/.emacs.d/= directory.  See Section "[[*.emacs.d/init.el][.emacs.d/init.el]]" for the contents of this file.
   - Note :: The =~= (tilde character) shorthand command refers to the user's /HOME/ directory.

2) This file (=emacs.org=) in the =~/.emacs.d/= directory.

3) The latest versions of Org-Mode (at least version 8) and Emacs (at least version 24.3) installed.  =init.el= expects to find the latest version of org-mode in =~/org-mode/=.
   - Note :: If the latest version of Org-Mode is not installed in the location above, then Emacs will use an older version of Org-Mode that is distributed with Emacs.  If Org-Mode is installed in a directory other than =~/org-mode/=, then change the variable =org-dir= in "[[*.emacs.d/init.el][.emacs.d/init.el]]" appropriately.

4) A =themes= directory within =~/.emacs.d/=, i.e. =~/.emacs.d/themes/=

5) A =bin= directory within /HOME/, i.e. =~/bin/=

6) A =site= directory within /HOME/, i.e. =~/site/=

7) Download and install the free [[http://dejavu-fonts.org/wiki/Main_Page][DejaVu]] fonts for a better Emacs experience.

** .emacs.d/init.el
1) Create the file =.emacs.d/init.el=, and copy the following into it.

   #+begin_example
     ;;; http://orgmode.org/worg/org-contrib/babel/intro.html
     ;;; init.el --- Where all the magic begins
     ;;
     (defvar dotfiles-dir (file-name-directory (or (buffer-file-name)
                                                   load-file-name)))
     
     ;; Set the directory for the latest version of org-mode
     (defvar org-dir (expand-file-name "org-mode" (expand-file-name "~/site")))
     (defvar org/lisp-dir (expand-file-name "lisp" org-dir))
     (defvar org/contrib-dir (expand-file-name "contrib/lisp" org-dir))
     (add-to-list 'load-path org/lisp-dir)
     (add-to-list 'load-path org/contrib-dir t)
     
     (defvar mswindows-p (string-match "windows" (symbol-name system-type)))
     (defvar macosx-p (string-match "darwin" (symbol-name system-type)))
     
     ;; Set the location of the repository
     (if mswindows-p
       (defvar use-git-repo 
         (expand-file-name "Documents/stb_main" (getenv "USERPROFILE"))))
     
     ;; Set the window (frame) size on startup
     (defvar *width* nil)
     (defvar *height* nil)
     (defvar *x-pos* 0)
     (defvar *y-pos* 0)
     
     (if (and (integerp *width*)
              (integerp *height*))
         (add-hook 'after-init-hook '(lambda () 
                                       (when window-system 
                                         (set-frame-size (selected-frame) 
                                                         ,*width* *height*))))
       (add-hook 'after-init-hook '(lambda () (w32-send-sys-command #xf030))))
     
     (when (and (integerp *x-pos*)
                (integerp *y-pos*))
       (set-frame-position (selected-frame) *x-pos* *y-pos*))
     
     (require 'org)
     (require 'org-install)
     (require 'ob-tangle)
     (require 'org-id)
     
     ;; Load up all literate org-mode files in this directory
     ;; In other words, load emacs.org
     (mapc #'org-babel-load-file (directory-files dotfiles-dir t "\\.org$"))
   #+end_example

* Keys
** General & Help
| Key Chord | Description                             | Command           |
|-----------+-----------------------------------------+-------------------|
| C-g       | Cancel current command.                 | keyboard-quit     |
| C-c h ?   | Help commands                           |                   |
| C-c h v   | Describe Variable                       | describe-variable |
| C-c h f   | Describe Function                       | describe-function |
| C-c h k   | Describe function bound to key chord    | describe-key      |
| C-c h h   | How to say "Hello" in various languages |                   |

** Cursor Movement
| Key Chord | Description                           | Command                                   |
|-----------+---------------------------------------+-------------------------------------------|
| C-f       | Forward one char                      | forward-char                              |
| C-b       | Backward one char                     | backward-char                             |
| M-f       | Forward word                          | forward-word                              |
| M-b       | Backward word                         | backward-word                             |
| M-e       | End of sentence, or table field       | org-forward-sentence / forward-sentence   |
| M-a       | Beginning of sentence, or table field | org-backward-sentence / backward-sentence |
| C-a       | Beginning of line                     | org-beginning-of-line                     |
| C-e       | End of line                           | org-end-of-line                           |
|           |                                       |                                           |
| C-p       | Up to previous line                   | previous-line                             |
| C-n       | Down to next line                     | next-line                                 |
| C-v       | Scroll screen down                    | cua-scroll-up                             |
| M-v       | Scroll screen up                      | cua-scroll-down                           |
| M->       | End of file                           | end-of-buffer                             |
| M-<       | Top of file                           | beginning-of-buffer                       |
| C-l       | Re-center screen on current line      | recenter-top-bottom                       |

** Editing Commands
| Key Chord      | Description                              | Command                   |
|----------------+------------------------------------------+---------------------------|
| C-z            | Undo                                     | undo                      |
| M-y            | Copy                                     | kill-ring-save            |
| M-y            | Paste                                    | cua-paste-pop / cua-paste |
| C-y            | Cut or "Yank" (not the American)         | org-yank                  |
|                |                                          |                           |
| C-h, BACKSPACE | Delete previous character                | org-delete-backward-char  |
| C-d, DEL       | Delete character forwards                | org-delete-char           |
| C-w            | Delete previous word                     | backward-kill-word        |
| M-d            | Delete forward word                      | kill-word                 |
| C-k            | Delete forward rest of line from cursor  | org-kill-line / kill-line |
|                |                                          |                           |
| M-c            | Capitalize word                          | capitalize-word           |
| M-u            | Uppercase word                           | upcase-word               |
|                |                                          |                           |
| C-q            | Read next input character and insert it. | quoted-insert             |

** File manipulation
| Key Chord | Description                                       | Command            |
|-----------+---------------------------------------------------+--------------------|
| C-x f     | List recently opened files                        | recentf-open-files |
