* System Customization
** Menu Bar, Tool Bar & Scroll Bars
The configuration file in =~/.emacs.d/emacs.org= specifies disables the Menu, Menu Bar, and Scroll Bar.  The Menu, Menu Bar, and Scroll Bar can be disabled or enabled within Emacs as follows;

1) Enter \keys{\Alt + x} =customize= (Alt-x =customize=), and
2) Search for and enable /Menu Bar/, /Scroll Bar/ & /Tool Bar/.
3) Apply and save changes.
   
To change the color theme;

1) Enter \keys{\Alt + x} =customize-themes= (Alt-x =customize-themes=), and
2) Choose a theme from the list of available themes.
3) Apply and save changes.
#+begin_src emacs-lisp
  ;; http://sites.google.com/site/steveyegge2/effective-emacs
  (if (fboundp 'scroll-bar-mode) (scroll-bar-mode -1)) ; Turn off the damn scroll bar
  (if (fboundp 'tool-bar-mode) (tool-bar-mode -1)) ;Turn off the damn tool bar
                                                   ;Note that in win32, this interferes with maximizing Emacs
  (when mswindows-p 
    (if (fboundp 'menu-bar-mode) (menu-bar-mode -1))) ;Turn off the menu bar
#+end_src

